         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translations</head>
            <div type="translation" source="#edd" xml:lang="en"> <p> Emperor Caesar, son of deified Trajan, victor in Parthia, grandson of deified Nerva, 
               Hadrian Augustus, high priest, holding tribunician power for the third time, consul for the third time <note>119 C.E.</note>,
            ordered that the bath-building, with the porticoes and the ball-courts and other associated structures 
            which were destroyed and burnt by the Jewish revolt, be restored for the city of the Cyrenians.</p></div>
       </div>
      
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>l.4 1st Jan. -9th Dec. 119. </p>
            <p>l.6 Oliverio, noted that the portico can be recognised beneath the Byzantine Baths to the south; 
               the Sphaeristera, he thought, may have been beside these or on an upper storey over the central area of the Baths of Trajan.</p>
         </div>
         
